{
  "texts": [
    "For example, biomedical KGs frequently over-represent common concepts while under-representing niche terms (Stephen et al., 2021).",
    "Our work addresses this gap by formalizing taxonomy integration as a first-class paradigm for KG construction, ensuring semantic consistency while preserving domain-specific nuance.",
    "LLMs excel in general-purpose information extraction (Gabriel et al., 2024; Pan et al., 2024 Pan et al.,, 2023;; Zhang et al., 2024), but struggle in scientific domains, exhibiting high hallucination for tail concepts (Viviane et al., 2024) and inconsistent recognition of domain-specific entities.",
    "Recent mitigations like contrastive decoding (Derong et al., 2024) and domain-adapted models (e.g., SciLitLLM (Sihang et al., 2024)) improve precision but remain taxonomy-agnostic.",
    "Our framework advances this paradigm by hard-constraining LLMs to predefined entity/relationship types from domain taxonomies."
  ]
}